						               													<description>In Get a Life, you want to assemble either the best or worst life possible from the cards available to you &amp;mdash; but which way you want to lean depends on the secret goal you receive at the start of the round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round one player is the &amp;quot;contestant&amp;quot;. Each other player receives one card in each of five categories &amp;mdash; companion, transportation, location, occupation, accommodation &amp;mdash; as well as a &amp;quot;Best&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;Worst&amp;quot; goal card. Players must reveal two of their five cards, then they use the &amp;quot;get a life&amp;quot; cards to acquire, steal or give away cards, all while trying to shape the &amp;quot;perfect&amp;quot; life. At round's end, the contestant judges which player has the best life and which has the worst &amp;mdash; and if these players have the right goal cards, they take a scoring chip.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Whoever ends up with the most scoring chips after a certain number of rounds wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
